{"pin":"BH03629","subcodes":[{"code":"BH03629","anchor":"","first_line":"This is an epistle from the Wronged One to one who hath been wronged, who hath drunk from the chalice of tribulation and tasted from the cup of adversity [3.5s]... ...Dispel my grief by Thy bounty and Thy generosity, O God, my God, and banish mine anguish through Thy sovereignty","first_line_orig":"این نامه ایست از مظلوم بسوی مظلومی که از کاس بلا آشامید و از کوب باساء چشید  ","language":"5","word_count":"240","subjects":"@prayers (general or uncategorized), @power and sovereignty of God; omnipotence of God, @prayer for assistance; intercession, @steadfastness; perseverance; faithfulness","notes":" \u003ca href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20070930181707/http://bahai-library.com/resources/leiden.list/leiden.list.html#507\"\u003eLL#507\u003c/a\u003e","translations":[]},{"code":"BH03629BOU","anchor":"bou","translations":[{"language":"sq","lang_name":"Albanian"}]},{"code":"BH03629GRI","anchor":"gri","translations":[{"language":"nl","lang_name":"Dutch"},{"language":"az","lang_name":"Azerbaijani"},{"language":"sk","lang_name":"Slovak"},{"language":"lv","lang_name":"Latvian"},{"language":"el","lang_name":"Greek"},{"language":"fi","lang_name":"Finnish"},{"language":"mn","lang_name":"Mongolian"},{"language":"cs","lang_name":"Czech"},{"language":"sv","lang_name":"Swedish"},{"language":"tl","lang_name":"Tagalog"},{"language":"tvl","lang_name":"Tuvalu"},{"language":"ca","lang_name":"Catalan"},{"language":"tr","lang_name":"Turkish"},{"language":"fr","lang_name":"French"},{"language":"mg","lang_name":"Malagasy"},{"language":"lg","lang_name":"Ganda"},{"language":"uk","lang_name":"Ukrainian"},{"language":"bg","lang_name":"Bulgarian"},{"language":"it","lang_name":"Italian"},{"language":"pl","lang_name":"Polish"},{"language":"hu","lang_name":"Hungarian"},{"language":"iba","lang_name":"Iban"},{"language":"kl","lang_name":"Kalaallisut"},{"language":"ky","lang_name":"Kirghiz"},{"language":"es","lang_name":"Spanish"